    "created_at": "2014-08-08T17:34:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-08T17:34:27Z",
    "body": "Okay I think I may have found the problematic code. I've tweaked one line and now Atom-Shell displays a minimize button for a window that is non-resizable. \n\nShouldn't the 'else' part of the 'if' look like:\n\n``` cpp\nstyle |= WS_MINIMIZEBOX;\n```\n\ninstead of:\n\n``` cpp\nstyle &= ~(WS_MAXIMIZEBOX | WS_MINIMIZEBOX | WS_THICKFRAME);\n```\n\nI'm thinking that just removes the maximize and minimize and resize handles which seems to be the behavior it does but I'm not a very good C++ or Windows programmer to be certain.\n\nHere is the full function which is contained in 'atom/browser/native_window_views.cc'\n\n``` cpp\nvoid NativeWindowViews::SetResizable(bool resizable) {\n  resizable_ = resizable;\n\n#if defined(OS_WIN)\n  if (has_frame_) {\n    // WS_MAXIMIZEBOX => Maximize button\n    // WS_MINIMIZEBOX => Minimize button\n    // WS_THICKFRAME => Resize handle\n    DWORD style = ::GetWindowLong(GetAcceleratedWidget(), GWL_STYLE);\n    if (resizable)\n      style |= WS_MAXIMIZEBOX | WS_MINIMIZEBOX | WS_THICKFRAME;\n    else\n      style &= ~(WS_MAXIMIZEBOX | WS_MINIMIZEBOX | WS_THICKFRAME);\n    ::SetWindowLong(GetAcceleratedWidget(), GWL_STYLE, style);\n  }\n#endif\n\n  // FIXME Implement me for X11.\n}\n```\n"
